@*
    Help documentation view for the PcApprovalAction component.
    Displays usage instructions and configuration guidance for the approval action buttons component
    in the WebVella page builder help panel.
*@

<h5><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Approval Action Component</h5>

<p>
    This component renders action buttons that allow authorized users to <strong>approve</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, 
    or <strong>delegate</strong> approval requests. When an action is performed, a modal dialog prompts for optional 
    or required comments before submitting the action to the approval workflow system.
</p>

<h6>Features</h6>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Approve Button:</strong> Marks the request as approved and advances the workflow to the next step.</li>
    <li><strong>Reject Button:</strong> Marks the request as rejected and ends the workflow. Comments are required.</li>
    <li><strong>Delegate Button:</strong> Reassigns the approval request to another user for review.</li>
    <li><strong>Comment Modal:</strong> Captures comments for audit trail when performing any action.</li>
</ul>

<h6>Configuration Options</h6>
<table class="table table-sm table-bordered">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Option</th>
            <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><code>request_id</code></td>
            <td>The approval request identifier. Use datasource binding to dynamically retrieve the request ID from the page context (e.g., from URL parameters or record data).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>show_approve_button</code></td>
            <td>Toggle visibility of the Approve button. Default: <code>true</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>show_reject_button</code></td>
            <td>Toggle visibility of the Reject button. Default: <code>true</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>show_delegate_button</code></td>
            <td>Toggle visibility of the Delegate button. Default: <code>true</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>require_comments_on_approve</code></td>
            <td>When enabled, requires the user to enter comments before approving. Default: <code>false</code></td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h6>Authorization</h6>
<p>
    Action buttons are only displayed when the current user is authorized to act on the request. 
    Authorization is determined by the workflow step configuration, which specifies allowed approvers 
    by user, role, or manager relationship.
</p>

<h6>Status Requirements</h6>
<p>
    Actions can only be performed on requests with a <strong>Pending</strong> status. Requests that have 
    already been approved, rejected, or cancelled will display the buttons in a disabled state.
</p>


